WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.084 --> 00:00:02.145
Hi.
This is a message for Elle Woods.

2
00:00:02.169 --> 00:00:04.231
You're a finalist
in the L.A. internship program.

3
00:00:04.255 --> 00:00:05.691
Yeah. this is huge!

4
00:00:05.715 --> 00:00:06.900
Previously on Elle...

5
00:00:06.924 --> 00:00:09.361
So. all I have to do is make
a groundbreaking video.

6
00:00:09.385 --> 00:00:11.321
I'll give Seattle
the best homecoming of all time.

7
00:00:11.345 --> 00:00:12.572
and I'll document the whole thing.

8
00:00:12.596 --> 00:00:14.408
Can you think of anything
more fun and fearless?

9
00:00:14.432 --> 00:00:16.743
I actually cannot.

10
00:00:16.767 --> 00:00:18.954
You've never done one here.

11
00:00:18.978 --> 00:00:20.038
Until now.

12
00:00:20.062 --> 00:00:21.206
This is so dumb.

13
00:00:21.230 --> 00:00:22.791
Homecoming wasn't a terrible idea.

14
00:00:22.815 --> 00:00:25.693
It might just not be like
an L.A. homecoming.

15
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:29.029
Maybe let them do it their way
instead of your way.

16
00:00:36.162 --> 00:00:37.806
Miles and I broke up last night.

17
00:00:37.830 --> 00:00:39.123
Wait. what?

18
00:00:40.666 --> 00:00:43.145
The big game is over. our fun...

19
00:00:43.169 --> 00:00:44.646
Oh. my God. Mom.

20
00:00:44.670 --> 00:00:46.440
This isn't footage. This is my life.

21
00:00:46.464 --> 00:00:50.634
I don't need to pretend to be
fun and fearless for a stupid video.

22
00:00:51.218 --> 00:00:53.679
I am fun and fearless.

23
00:00:57.516 --> 00:00:59.536
Hey. hey. have you seen Shannon?

24
00:00:59.560 --> 00:01:01.854
Shannon's mom was in
a car accident last night.

25
00:01:02.480 --> 00:01:03.773
She's dead.

26
00:01:14.950 --> 00:01:16.911
Oh. my God. Shannon's here.

27
00:01:28.255 --> 00:01:30.883
I didn't expect her
to be back at school so soon.

28
00:01:31.467 --> 00:01:33.844
It's probably good for her
to be around friends right now.

29
00:01:34.428 --> 00:01:36.305
I don't know if that includes me.

30
00:01:37.848 --> 00:01:40.535
Kissing Miles feels like
an even bigger betrayal now.

31
00:01:40.559 --> 00:01:42.662
You couldn't have known
this was going to happen.

32
00:01:42.686 --> 00:01:44.164
I just don't know how I'm gonna tell her.

33
00:01:44.188 --> 00:01:45.665
-Oh. honey. you're not.
-Wh...

34
00:01:45.689 --> 00:01:47.667
No. At least not right now.

35
00:01:47.691 --> 00:01:50.587
First kisses are monumental
for the two people involved.

36
00:01:50.611 --> 00:01:54.532
but what Shannon is dealing with.
so much bigger.

37
00:01:55.241 --> 00:01:58.053
She doesn't have any more room
on her plate right now.

38
00:01:58.077 --> 00:02:01.598
You're right. She just needs a friend.

39
00:02:01.622 --> 00:02:05.751
And no one is a better friend
to lean on than Elle Woods.

40
00:02:07.628 --> 00:02:10.023
I have no idea how I'm gonna help her.

41
00:02:10.047 --> 00:02:11.674
You'll find a way.

42
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:17.948
Now. remember. anything
can happen at any moment.

43
00:02:17.972 --> 00:02:19.199
No one is owed a tomorrow.

44
00:02:19.223 --> 00:02:22.661
Stop using your own mortality
to guilt me into a goodbye hug.

45
00:02:22.685 --> 00:02:25.938
Do you really want that to be
the last thing you say to your mother?

46
00:02:32.862 --> 00:02:33.946
Whatever. I love you.

47
00:02:44.498 --> 00:02:47.227
I am so glad you're here.

48
00:02:47.251 --> 00:02:48.544
I'm here.

49
00:02:52.339 --> 00:02:55.009
I'm so sorry about your mom.

50
00:02:57.011 --> 00:03:00.866
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

51
00:03:00.890 --> 00:03:03.976
♪ I'm only happy when it's complicated ♪

52
00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:06.955
♪ And though I know you can't ♪

53
00:03:06.979 --> 00:03:08.957
♪ appreciate it ♪

54
00:03:08.981 --> 00:03:12.401
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

55
00:03:13.152 --> 00:03:15.005
♪ Pour your ♪

56
00:03:15.029 --> 00:03:17.632
-♪ misery down ♪
-♪ Pour your misery down ♪

57
00:03:17.656 --> 00:03:21.011
-♪ Pour your misery down on me ♪
-♪ Pour your misery down ♪

58
00:03:21.035 --> 00:03:25.015
-♪ Pour your misery down ♪
-♪ Pour your misery down ♪

59
00:03:25.039 --> 00:03:29.019
♪ You can keep me company as long as ♪

60
00:03:29.043 --> 00:03:31.045
♪ you don't care ♪

61
00:03:33.130 --> 00:03:36.342
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

62
00:03:37.134 --> 00:03:40.363
♪ You wanna hear about my new obsession? ♪

63
00:03:40.387 --> 00:03:42.365
♪ I'm riding high upon ♪

64
00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:44.826
♪ a deep depression ♪

65
00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:47.287
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

66
00:03:47.311 --> 00:03:50.832
♪ Pour some misery down on me ♪

67
00:03:50.856 --> 00:03:53.126
♪ I'm only happy when it rains ♪

68
00:03:53.150 --> 00:03:57.112
♪ Pour some misery down on me ♪

69
00:04:04.995 --> 00:04:06.473
Good morning. everyone.

70
00:04:06.497 --> 00:04:09.643
Uh... well. I know this is chemistry.

71
00:04:09.667 --> 00:04:12.020
but since this is our first class back

72
00:04:12.044 --> 00:04:16.775
after the tragic news
about Ms. Walker. I thought.

73
00:04:16.799 --> 00:04:19.402
I don't know. we could put a pin
in science for once

74
00:04:19.426 --> 00:04:21.720
and talk about feelings.

75
00:04:23.764 --> 00:04:24.991
Okay. I'll start.

76
00:04:25.015 --> 00:04:29.120
My first experience with loss
is when my grandma died.

77
00:04:29.144 --> 00:04:32.666
Yeah. I was nine. and I'd collected
all these seashells at Puget Sound

78
00:04:32.690 --> 00:04:35.484
to give her as a Christmas gift.
but she passed before I could.

79
00:04:36.986 --> 00:04:39.613
I still have that box
of shells all wrapped up in my closet.

80
00:04:40.197 --> 00:04:42.008
She was a very cruel woman.

81
00:04:42.032 --> 00:04:46.620
but... still... related. so...

82
00:04:47.246 --> 00:04:49.474
Uh. show of hands. um.

83
00:04:49.498 --> 00:04:51.333
anyone else experienced loss before?

84
00:04:52.001 --> 00:04:52.978
Yes. Alison.

85
00:04:53.002 --> 00:04:54.378
Our family cat.

86
00:04:55.546 --> 00:04:57.023
Mm. Jacob.

87
00:04:57.047 --> 00:04:59.734
Uh. does Jerry Garcia count?

88
00:04:59.758 --> 00:05:03.053
Absolutely. [chuckles] Yes.

89
00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:05.471
Yes. Dustin.

90
00:05:06.807 --> 00:05:11.913
My grandma. She was... very honest.

91
00:05:11.937 --> 00:05:13.790
Best person I ever met.

92
00:05:13.814 --> 00:05:17.168
That's a very admirable quality.

93
00:05:17.192 --> 00:05:18.610
I'm sorry.

94
00:05:25.075 --> 00:05:27.637
Oh. Elle. who have you lost?

95
00:05:27.661 --> 00:05:28.787
Oh.

96
00:05:29.913 --> 00:05:31.599
No one.

97
00:05:31.623 --> 00:05:33.917
May I use the pass. please?

98
00:05:51.769 --> 00:05:53.705
"Cinco de Mayo."

99
00:05:53.729 --> 00:05:55.415
"Smooth jazz."

100
00:05:55.439 --> 00:05:56.774
"Pumpkin patch"?

101
00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:05.258
Robin's funeral will be in Denver
where most of her family lives.

102
00:06:05.282 --> 00:06:07.761
but Shannon felt like
so many people here loved Robin

103
00:06:07.785 --> 00:06:09.888
and would want to say goodbye.
so I panicked

104
00:06:09.912 --> 00:06:11.997
and offered to throw her a memorial.

105
00:06:13.749 --> 00:06:15.018
"Bobblehead Fridays."

106
00:06:15.042 --> 00:06:19.254
And then stupidly asked the student body
for theme suggestions.

107
00:06:23.217 --> 00:06:24.944
-This one just says "water slide."
-Yep.

108
00:06:24.968 --> 00:06:26.887
They're all like that.

109
00:06:28.097 --> 00:06:30.408
Oh. this one's not too bad.

110
00:06:30.432 --> 00:06:32.267
This one says I could help you plan it.

111
00:06:34.061 --> 00:06:35.914
-Okay. it doesn't. but I could.
-Mm.

112
00:06:35.938 --> 00:06:38.083
Why would you help me?

113
00:06:38.107 --> 00:06:40.150
Honestly. it'd be helping me.

114
00:06:41.068 --> 00:06:42.670
Everyone else seems to know what to do.

115
00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:45.715
The only death I've ever experienced
is Hope in Days of Our Lives.

116
00:06:45.739 --> 00:06:49.344
and I petitioned NBC
till they brought her back from the dead.

117
00:06:49.368 --> 00:06:51.805
I just feel like I need to do something.

118
00:06:51.829 --> 00:06:55.100
You met Shannon's mom
for. like. two seconds.

119
00:06:55.124 --> 00:06:56.434
You'll be fine.

120
00:06:56.458 --> 00:06:57.668
Okay. but what about you?

121
00:06:58.752 --> 00:07:01.064
You're Shannon's best friend.

122
00:07:01.088 --> 00:07:03.566
I bet Robin meant a lot to you.

123
00:07:03.590 --> 00:07:07.678
You deserve to be able to go mourn
without having to worry about logistics.

124
00:07:09.179 --> 00:07:10.889
Let me help.

125
00:07:13.976 --> 00:07:16.996
Okay. Um...

126
00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:22.168
If. theoretically.
you were gonna help with this.

127
00:07:22.192 --> 00:07:23.753
what would you be thinking about doing?

128
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:25.839
First things first. we would need a venue.

129
00:07:25.863 --> 00:07:29.384
Something that says "free spirit."
but with class.

130
00:07:29.408 --> 00:07:30.760
I'm assuming there's no budget.

131
00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:32.011
Twelve hundred dollars.

132
00:07:32.035 --> 00:07:35.431
Leave it to me to hone in
on the perfect setting.

133
00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:37.291
You go be with Shannon and grieve.

134
00:07:39.334 --> 00:07:40.627
Thank you.

135
00:07:46.592 --> 00:07:50.989
Wyatt Woods one.
Lake Washington Loop zero.

136
00:07:51.013 --> 00:07:52.681
Ah.

137
00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:58.562
That's a stormier motif
than you usually go with.

138
00:07:59.313 --> 00:08:00.290
Is it?

139
00:08:00.314 --> 00:08:01.332
Yeah.

140
00:08:01.356 --> 00:08:02.524
Oh. God.

141
00:08:04.985 --> 00:08:08.173
Did you know Robin
was only two months older than me?

142
00:08:08.197 --> 00:08:11.718
Also the middle child.
Also an early bloomer.

143
00:08:11.742 --> 00:08:13.344
-You read the book.
-No.

144
00:08:13.368 --> 00:08:14.304
Oh.

145
00:08:14.328 --> 00:08:17.473
It was way too long.
but I just think it's crazy. like.

146
00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:21.501
someone like that can be gone
in an instant.

147
00:08:22.252 --> 00:08:26.816
Here I am giving Elle life advice.
and her own mother hasn't even lived.

148
00:08:26.840 --> 00:08:30.528
But you've laughed and loved.
And you're breathing.

149
00:08:30.552 --> 00:08:31.821
-so you're living.
-What?

150
00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:35.557
Don't you remember?
She inscribed the-the. um. book. Here.

151
00:08:37.267 --> 00:08:39.746
-"Eva. live. laugh. love. Robin."
-Oh.

152
00:08:39.770 --> 00:08:42.040
Talk about living.
That's a pretty good guidebook.

153
00:08:42.064 --> 00:08:44.459
She hiked Mount Kilimanjaro
when she was 12.

154
00:08:44.483 --> 00:08:46.419
-Mm.
-We have a big. beautiful

155
00:08:46.443 --> 00:08:48.379
mountain in our backyard
just begging to be climbed.

156
00:08:48.403 --> 00:08:50.673
Yeah. but do you remember
I got altitude poisoning in Vail?

157
00:08:50.697 --> 00:08:53.551
I know. but Mount Rainier has been on
my must-do list since we moved here.

158
00:08:53.575 --> 00:08:55.178
I'll tell you what. I'll get the poles.

159
00:08:55.202 --> 00:08:56.471
and you fill up the water bladders.

160
00:08:56.495 --> 00:08:59.974
Oh. God. So. I think maybe
I'll just walk Bruiser

161
00:08:59.998 --> 00:09:01.893
'cause Maple Street is very hilly.

162
00:09:01.917 --> 00:09:03.877
Eva. we are doing this.

163
00:09:04.461 --> 00:09:07.482
We are living. we are laughing.
we are loving life.

164
00:09:07.506 --> 00:09:11.051
God. I'm thirsty just thinking about it.
Will you pack me an extra bladder?

165
00:09:26.650 --> 00:09:29.212
Excuse me. Are you lost?

166
00:09:29.236 --> 00:09:33.049
Hey. I am not the one who's supposed to be
in algebra right now.

167
00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:38.578
Turns out... solving for X
felt wildly insignificant today.

168
00:09:39.579 --> 00:09:40.556
What brings you out here?

169
00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:42.600
Wait for it.

170
00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:45.812
I'm helping Kimberly
plan Robin's memorial.

171
00:09:45.836 --> 00:09:49.023
I'm sorry. I thought you just said
you're helping Kimberly.

172
00:09:49.047 --> 00:09:51.985
She was flailing. I was flailing.

173
00:09:52.009 --> 00:09:54.303
And it's a way to be there for Shannon.

174
00:09:55.304 --> 00:09:58.324
Though I'm not feeling this field
for a paper lantern launch.

175
00:09:58.348 --> 00:10:01.852
so striking that from the maybe list.

176
00:10:06.023 --> 00:10:07.190
How are you holding up?

177
00:10:09.568 --> 00:10:11.236
I knew Robin since I was a kid.

178
00:10:12.529 --> 00:10:13.798
That's a lot of memories.

179
00:10:13.822 --> 00:10:16.116
She was really good to me
for a really long time.

180
00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:22.414
She called me after Shannon and I broke up
to say she was thinking about me.

181
00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:26.835
I never called her back.

182
00:10:28.003 --> 00:10:29.421
I'm so sorry.

183
00:10:34.051 --> 00:10:35.778
It's not that I don't want
to hold your hand.

184
00:10:35.802 --> 00:10:38.013
-I get it.
-I just want to do it right.

185
00:10:39.514 --> 00:10:42.994
I'll talk to Shannon.
face-to-face. girl-to-girl.

186
00:10:43.018 --> 00:10:44.519
and I'll tell her that we kissed.

187
00:10:45.395 --> 00:10:46.914
And then what?

188
00:10:46.938 --> 00:10:49.250
And then...

189
00:10:49.274 --> 00:10:51.693
I'll gauge her reaction
and we'll go from there.

190
00:10:52.819 --> 00:10:56.174
But now is obviously not the time.

191
00:10:56.198 --> 00:10:58.384
So until the appropriate time
presents itself.

192
00:10:58.408 --> 00:11:01.346
we need to put a moratorium
on any more bodily contact.

193
00:11:01.370 --> 00:11:03.163
Sure.

194
00:11:06.166 --> 00:11:08.877
I'll. uh... I'll see you.

195
00:11:22.891 --> 00:11:26.895
Hey. Mom? Do you remember the name
of the florist who did Jackie O's funeral?

196
00:11:27.813 --> 00:11:31.084
Oh. And why do you look like
Laura Dern in Jurassic Park?

197
00:11:31.108 --> 00:11:34.796
Honey. um. I know
you've had a lot going on lately.

198
00:11:34.820 --> 00:11:37.673
but did you forget to tell me
we had a visitor?

199
00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:40.676
-A visitor?
-The rumors are true.

200
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:43.787
Madison LeDoux is in Seattle. baby. Whoo!

201
00:11:46.081 --> 00:11:47.916
Yeah. You're here.

202
00:11:51.711 --> 00:11:53.046
Of course I'm here.

203
00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:55.942
Because it's fall break.

204
00:11:55.966 --> 00:11:58.694
which is right after
the parties of Halloween

205
00:11:58.718 --> 00:12:00.530
and right before the obligations
of the holidays.

206
00:12:00.554 --> 00:12:01.614
-Yes.
-Which is now.

207
00:12:01.638 --> 00:12:03.741
You're here.

208
00:12:03.765 --> 00:12:06.202
-Oh. I missed you.
-Oh. I missed you. too.

209
00:12:06.226 --> 00:12:08.788
I wasn't sure what November
in Seattle is like.

210
00:12:08.812 --> 00:12:10.915
so I had my stylist pack a wide range.

211
00:12:10.939 --> 00:12:12.667
Well. I think it's supposed to rain today.

212
00:12:12.691 --> 00:12:14.252
Is that why your hair looks like that?

213
00:12:14.276 --> 00:12:15.628
What do you mean?

214
00:12:15.652 --> 00:12:18.005
Oh. no. It's just...

215
00:12:18.029 --> 00:12:22.718
your hair is looking a little more Seattle
than I think your L.A. self would want.

216
00:12:22.742 --> 00:12:24.411
Let me try to fix it.

217
00:12:26.246 --> 00:12:27.414
Oh. okay.

218
00:12:31.001 --> 00:12:32.669
Um...

219
00:12:34.129 --> 00:12:38.025
Seattle is... stubborn.

220
00:12:38.049 --> 00:12:39.694
I missed you.

221
00:12:39.718 --> 00:12:41.863
There's no one here to tell me
when my outer being

222
00:12:41.887 --> 00:12:43.698
no longer aligns with my inner spirit.

223
00:12:43.722 --> 00:12:45.158
Mm.

224
00:12:45.182 --> 00:12:48.786
Okay. So. itinerary-wise.
I've come up with a list of must-sees.

225
00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:53.124
but I'm sure that you found some hidden
gems that you're planning to show me.

226
00:12:53.148 --> 00:12:56.544
For sure. [laughs] The gem-iest.

227
00:12:56.568 --> 00:12:59.255
But I'd love to take
a quick peek at your list.

228
00:12:59.279 --> 00:13:02.300
Always fun to cross-reference.

229
00:13:02.324 --> 00:13:04.260
We need some music.

230
00:13:04.284 --> 00:13:07.388
♪ Close your eyes...

231
00:13:07.412 --> 00:13:09.206
This is what
you're listening to?

232
00:13:09.789 --> 00:13:11.934
It's a song for the memorial
I'm helping plan.

233
00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:13.394
♪ Do you feel my heart beating? ♪

234
00:13:13.418 --> 00:13:14.628
For Shannon's mom.

235
00:13:15.128 --> 00:13:16.564
Shannon's mom died?

236
00:13:16.588 --> 00:13:17.982
♪ Do you understand...

237
00:13:18.006 --> 00:13:19.734
That's so sad.

238
00:13:19.758 --> 00:13:21.652
I know.

239
00:13:21.676 --> 00:13:24.655
The poor woman summited Annapurna
without oxygen.

240
00:13:24.679 --> 00:13:27.474
but then died in a car wreck.

241
00:13:29.434 --> 00:13:31.478
That's so tragic.

242
00:13:32.270 --> 00:13:33.897
I'm really sorry. Elle.

243
00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:38.669
But on the bright side.
the last time we talked.

244
00:13:38.693 --> 00:13:40.963
you were obsessed
with becoming friends with Shannon.

245
00:13:40.987 --> 00:13:43.424
and if you're planning
a memorial for her mom.

246
00:13:43.448 --> 00:13:46.385
then. clearly. you've made it
to friend status.

247
00:13:46.409 --> 00:13:49.013
♪ Do you feel the same? ♪

248
00:13:49.037 --> 00:13:53.351
♪ Am I only dreaming...

249
00:13:53.375 --> 00:13:58.439
You know. there's this
super cool record store

250
00:13:58.463 --> 00:14:01.442
that you don't have on your list.

251
00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:03.510
I mean. if you wanted authentic Seattle.

252
00:14:04.094 --> 00:14:06.489
See? I knew you'd have a hidden gem.

253
00:14:06.513 --> 00:14:08.598
♪ Do you feel my heart...

254
00:14:13.228 --> 00:14:15.039
There's my favorite coffee shop.

255
00:14:15.063 --> 00:14:17.959
Sweetie. that's a Starbucks.
They're literally everywhere.

256
00:14:17.983 --> 00:14:20.193
It's more authentic closer to the source.

257
00:14:20.902 --> 00:14:24.090
What about the big needle
everyone talks about?

258
00:14:24.114 --> 00:14:27.677
Yes. The Space Needle opened in 1962
for the World's Fair.

259
00:14:27.701 --> 00:14:30.638
Dubbed the 400-day wonder
because it was built in 400 days.

260
00:14:30.662 --> 00:14:31.847
We should check it out.

261
00:14:31.871 --> 00:14:33.915
Mm. Seems a little generic for Robin.

262
00:14:34.583 --> 00:14:36.394
Oh. Why would Robin care?

263
00:14:36.418 --> 00:14:39.522
Oh. sorry. I thought you meant
for the memorial.

264
00:14:39.546 --> 00:14:43.526
No. I mean we should check it out.
for ourselves.

265
00:14:43.550 --> 00:14:45.611
Honey. you're gonna find the right venue.

266
00:14:45.635 --> 00:14:49.240
I'm sure Robin had a lot
of really meaningful places in her life.

267
00:14:49.264 --> 00:14:52.785
Robin lived in the Hoh Rain Forest
for six months. She ate bugs.

268
00:14:52.809 --> 00:14:54.954
Don't be revolting.

269
00:14:54.978 --> 00:14:56.455
You and Kimberly are gonna find something.

270
00:14:56.479 --> 00:15:00.751
I'm sorry. your party co-planner is the B
who wrote S on your locker?

271
00:15:00.775 --> 00:15:01.919
-What?
-Nothing.

272
00:15:01.943 --> 00:15:04.589
-Bitch who wrote "slut."
-Some B wrote that word on your I?

273
00:15:04.613 --> 00:15:06.924
-Sweetie. Mm. Mm-mm.
-Well. that was early fall.

274
00:15:06.948 --> 00:15:09.385
We're now in late fall. pre-winter.

275
00:15:09.409 --> 00:15:11.703
And she needed space for her own grief.

276
00:15:13.538 --> 00:15:15.457
Could you take a left up here?

277
00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:27.695
Wow.

278
00:15:27.719 --> 00:15:32.116
This place is so... cute.

279
00:15:32.140 --> 00:15:34.976
Madison. meet Liz. Liz. meet Madison.

280
00:15:37.604 --> 00:15:38.605
From L.A.

281
00:15:39.564 --> 00:15:42.501
Um. Madison was just saying
how cute this place is.

282
00:15:42.525 --> 00:15:44.295
Cute?

283
00:15:44.319 --> 00:15:46.756
Yeah. Like it's from Reality Bites.

284
00:15:46.780 --> 00:15:49.884
I don't think they go to a record store
in Reality Bites.

285
00:15:49.908 --> 00:15:55.497
Never saw it. but I consider Winona Ryder
a friend and a mentor.

286
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:02.688
Liz. I was wondering if you could maybe
make a mix tape for Robin's memorial?

287
00:16:02.712 --> 00:16:05.858
-Hmm.
-Think "Eternal Flame."

288
00:16:05.882 --> 00:16:08.009
but. like. more songs.

289
00:16:10.679 --> 00:16:13.324
I thought we were here
so you could show me a hidden gem.

290
00:16:13.348 --> 00:16:14.950
We are.

291
00:16:14.974 --> 00:16:18.079
But two birds. one gem.

292
00:16:18.103 --> 00:16:20.456
I figured while we're here. I'd ask.

293
00:16:20.480 --> 00:16:22.708
You came to the right place.

294
00:16:22.732 --> 00:16:27.380
Yo. Liz. Just got a new shipment of. uh...
better music than yours.

295
00:16:27.404 --> 00:16:29.906
Shut up. Todd.

296
00:16:30.490 --> 00:16:32.301
-Who was that?
-Oh. that's my boss.

297
00:16:32.325 --> 00:16:35.286
-So. what's the attire for the memorial?
-Grief chic.

298
00:16:35.870 --> 00:16:38.057
I am even more confused than before.

299
00:16:38.081 --> 00:16:39.767
I've never really been to a memorial.

300
00:16:39.791 --> 00:16:41.852
It doesn't matter what you wear.

301
00:16:41.876 --> 00:16:44.129
It only matters what you wear.

302
00:16:48.508 --> 00:16:49.801
I know that.

303
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:54.532
You know what we need?

304
00:16:54.556 --> 00:16:56.033
Less Seattle.

305
00:16:56.057 --> 00:16:59.412
-more BFF-143-637.
-Six-three-seven.

306
00:16:59.436 --> 00:17:00.687
Excuse... What?

307
00:17:01.271 --> 00:17:05.191
Oh. you don't know pager code?
Bummer.

308
00:17:15.034 --> 00:17:17.638
Person. place or thing?

309
00:17:17.662 --> 00:17:20.391
Person. But. like. almost a thing.

310
00:17:20.415 --> 00:17:22.977
Hot Josh is trying to grow a mustache.

311
00:17:23.001 --> 00:17:24.270
Oh.

312
00:17:24.294 --> 00:17:26.355
We've been calling him Tepid Josh.

313
00:17:26.379 --> 00:17:29.191
Oh. no. Is it wispy?

314
00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:31.193
Tiffany saw him brushing it.

315
00:17:31.217 --> 00:17:32.903
Gross!

316
00:17:32.927 --> 00:17:35.865
How do you feel about having
your first kiss with a wispy stache?

317
00:17:35.889 --> 00:17:38.993
Well. technically. it would be
my second kiss.

318
00:17:39.017 --> 00:17:41.328
Wait. what? What are you talking about?

319
00:17:41.352 --> 00:17:43.748
What? What?

320
00:17:43.772 --> 00:17:44.832
I kissed Miles.

321
00:17:44.856 --> 00:17:46.792
How was that not the first thing

322
00:17:46.816 --> 00:17:49.128
out of your mouth
the very first moment you saw me?

323
00:17:49.152 --> 00:17:52.256
-It's not a big deal.
-It's the biggest deal.

324
00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:54.574
This is a pivotal life moment.

325
00:17:55.867 --> 00:17:57.118
What else has happened?

326
00:17:59.871 --> 00:18:02.141
I guess...

327
00:18:02.165 --> 00:18:05.770
it just doesn't feel quite as epic
since Robin died.

328
00:18:05.794 --> 00:18:07.730
Okay.

329
00:18:07.754 --> 00:18:10.900
Well. I understand
if you can't exactly be throwing

330
00:18:10.924 --> 00:18:12.610
a "I had my first kiss" party

331
00:18:12.634 --> 00:18:16.906
when your co-kisser's ex-girlfriend
is in mourning. but...

332
00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:19.575
this is me.

333
00:18:19.599 --> 00:18:22.912
We pretended to marry Patrick Swayze
when we were ten.

334
00:18:22.936 --> 00:18:27.023
We practiced kissing Emilio Estevez
on the backs of our hands.

335
00:18:28.691 --> 00:18:31.212
I guess I'm just not
in a celebratory place.

336
00:18:31.236 --> 00:18:34.715
See. this is why I don't get Seattle.

337
00:18:34.739 --> 00:18:36.991
Everything has a rain cloud over it.

338
00:18:38.785 --> 00:18:40.245
Okay.

339
00:18:42.163 --> 00:18:46.227
Glass half-full. when you come back
to L.A. for the internship

340
00:18:46.251 --> 00:18:48.187
that you are so obviously going to win.

341
00:18:48.211 --> 00:18:51.422
you'll have already had your first kiss
under your belt.

342
00:18:55.802 --> 00:18:58.197
Uh. want to watch Sleepless in Seattle?

343
00:18:58.221 --> 00:19:02.660
Yes. Now. that's a version
of Seattle I can get behind.

344
00:19:02.684 --> 00:19:05.120
Tom Hanks could never be tepid.

345
00:19:05.144 --> 00:19:08.147
-No. he can't.
-I don't think it's possible.

346
00:19:10.775 --> 00:19:14.004
I know what you're thinking:
"What's the catch?"

347
00:19:14.028 --> 00:19:16.632
An aquarium would be
a wonderful space for a memorial.

348
00:19:16.656 --> 00:19:20.427
Robin had her spiritual awakening
among the sea turtles in the Gili Islands.

349
00:19:20.451 --> 00:19:23.556
but the only availability was at midnight
in two Sundays.

350
00:19:23.580 --> 00:19:25.558
Most of the fish
would be asleep.

351
00:19:25.582 --> 00:19:27.393
-Yeah.
-I think we can

352
00:19:27.417 --> 00:19:30.336
eliminate this option
due to timing constraints.

353
00:19:31.713 --> 00:19:33.148
So. that leaves us with

354
00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:34.817
a garden gathering at Chez Woods.

355
00:19:34.841 --> 00:19:37.444
or my personal favorite.

356
00:19:37.468 --> 00:19:40.364
we take a literal page from Robin's book

357
00:19:40.388 --> 00:19:43.117
and honor her memory
in the place she called

358
00:19:43.141 --> 00:19:48.038
her "favorite spot on this big.
beautiful. orbiting rock we call Earth."

359
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:49.522
Presenting...

360
00:19:51.316 --> 00:19:53.860
the rainforest.

361
00:19:57.614 --> 00:20:02.887
So... everyone just stands around outside
all sad. getting rained on?

362
00:20:02.911 --> 00:20:06.724
I knew you'd say that. which is why...
Drum roll.

363
00:20:06.748 --> 00:20:08.267
-Not gonna happen.
-Okay.

364
00:20:08.291 --> 00:20:10.686
Cuing up internal drum roll.

365
00:20:10.710 --> 00:20:12.420
The Rainforest...

366
00:20:15.173 --> 00:20:16.799
Cafe.

367
00:20:18.551 --> 00:20:20.696
There's no way they'll book
for a group event so last minute.

368
00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:22.865
They will if you call 150 times

369
00:20:22.889 --> 00:20:24.891
and make reservations
using different voices.

370
00:20:25.558 --> 00:20:27.328
I did realize pretty quickly

371
00:20:27.352 --> 00:20:29.997
the only way I know how
to throw my voice is to lean into

372
00:20:30.021 --> 00:20:31.898
celebrity impressions.

373
00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:35.318
That was Dick Van Dyke.

374
00:20:36.945 --> 00:20:38.404
From Mary Poppins.

375
00:20:39.280 --> 00:20:42.176
Never mind. I've created
a simple name tag system

376
00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:45.304
we can utilize day of
so no one's the wiser.

377
00:20:45.328 --> 00:20:46.788
Anyway. we're booked.

378
00:20:49.707 --> 00:20:53.086
That is so...

379
00:20:55.213 --> 00:20:56.214
genius.

380
00:20:57.298 --> 00:20:59.526
God. I'm so mad you just gave me
a reason to call you a genius.

381
00:20:59.550 --> 00:21:01.094
Group effort.

382
00:21:03.262 --> 00:21:04.472
Okay.

383
00:21:07.850 --> 00:21:11.038
Happy Space Needle Friday.

384
00:21:11.062 --> 00:21:13.666
Oh. tonight is gonna be
some varsity-level touristing.

385
00:21:13.690 --> 00:21:16.669
-Oh. yeah.
-I mean. after our. as Elle put it.

386
00:21:16.693 --> 00:21:18.212
cameo at the memorial.

387
00:21:18.236 --> 00:21:21.131
-Mm-hmm. Yes.
-First stop. Space Needle.

388
00:21:21.155 --> 00:21:23.509
Then to the Sleepless in Seattle
houseboat.

389
00:21:23.533 --> 00:21:25.636
and then to some place
where they throw fish at us.

390
00:21:25.660 --> 00:21:29.098
Pike Place. Your one-stop shop
for locally sourced artisan fare.

391
00:21:29.122 --> 00:21:31.266
It'll be good to give Elle
the full Seattle experience

392
00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:32.351
before she goes back to L.A.

393
00:21:32.375 --> 00:21:34.603
-She's going back to L.A.?
-For the Cosmo internship.

394
00:21:34.627 --> 00:21:36.105
Oh. no. that's not
happening anymore. No. no.

395
00:21:36.129 --> 00:21:38.941
She was a finalist.
then she threw out her application.

396
00:21:38.965 --> 00:21:40.609
And that was even before
a Space Needle visit.

397
00:21:40.633 --> 00:21:43.654
I'm telling you. Seattle grows on you.

398
00:21:43.678 --> 00:21:47.890
I guess I didn't realize
she wasn't coming home.

399
00:21:53.688 --> 00:21:54.957
What's wrong?

400
00:21:54.981 --> 00:21:59.044
I know you said Robin swore by
the enlightening benefits of meditation.

401
00:21:59.068 --> 00:22:02.613
but I was just alone with my thoughts
for 17 minutes.

402
00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:07.035
It was unbearable.

403
00:22:16.711 --> 00:22:18.713
-Are you making her do it. too?
-Hmm?

404
00:22:19.672 --> 00:22:21.841
♪ Is this burning ♪

405
00:22:23.926 --> 00:22:26.447
♪ an eternal flame? ♪

406
00:22:26.471 --> 00:22:28.907
♪ Say my name ♪

407
00:22:28.931 --> 00:22:32.411
♪ Sun shines through the rain.
a whole life...

408
00:22:32.435 --> 00:22:36.790
So. this is what Burbank
looks like?

409
00:22:36.814 --> 00:22:39.460
Because there's
a Rainforest Cafe in Burbank.

410
00:22:39.484 --> 00:22:42.129
We should go when you're back in L.A.

411
00:22:42.153 --> 00:22:43.654
Totally.

412
00:22:48.701 --> 00:22:51.555
This is bonkers.

413
00:22:51.579 --> 00:22:53.307
Oh. no. Is it?

414
00:22:53.331 --> 00:22:54.975
I love it.

415
00:22:54.999 --> 00:22:56.226
Thank God.

416
00:22:56.250 --> 00:22:58.103
Nancy Kerrigan.

417
00:22:58.127 --> 00:23:01.106
My mom was obsessed with
figure skating. How did you know that?

418
00:23:01.130 --> 00:23:03.484
I caught the Lillehammer reference
in the book's footnotes.

419
00:23:03.508 --> 00:23:05.360
-Oh.
-Oh.

420
00:23:05.384 --> 00:23:07.196
Ashley Olsen?

421
00:23:07.220 --> 00:23:08.513
"You got it. dude."

422
00:23:09.347 --> 00:23:13.476
Everything's perfect. Elle.
I didn't know how much I needed this.

423
00:23:14.769 --> 00:23:16.330
And thank you for being here.

424
00:23:16.354 --> 00:23:19.565
I'm sure this was the last thing
you wanted to do on your fall break.

425
00:23:20.149 --> 00:23:22.151
I'm just happy to see my best friend.

426
00:23:23.903 --> 00:23:25.839
I'm so sorry for your loss.

427
00:23:25.863 --> 00:23:28.008
I appreciate that.

428
00:23:28.032 --> 00:23:32.328
Oh. My mom's publisher is here.
I need to go say hi.

429
00:23:34.413 --> 00:23:37.810
Mm. I see the appeal.

430
00:23:37.834 --> 00:23:39.293
She seems really strong.

431
00:23:40.545 --> 00:23:42.689
Anyway. should we call your dad
to come pick us up?

432
00:23:42.713 --> 00:23:45.067
One sec. I think Kimberly
just went off-book.

433
00:23:45.091 --> 00:23:47.611
♪ Is this burning...

434
00:23:47.635 --> 00:23:49.613
Okay.

435
00:23:49.637 --> 00:23:53.349
I'll just circulate on my own.

436
00:23:57.645 --> 00:24:01.291
♪ Do you feel my heart beating? ♪

437
00:24:01.315 --> 00:24:03.818
♪ Do you understand? ♪

438
00:24:10.992 --> 00:24:12.761
Screech.

439
00:24:12.785 --> 00:24:14.555
I thought for sure
I grabbed Christian Slater.

440
00:24:14.579 --> 00:24:16.306
We're only at a memorial.

441
00:24:16.330 --> 00:24:19.125
but cool if that's the hardest thing
going on in your life right now.

442
00:24:24.463 --> 00:24:25.524
Oh. my God.

443
00:24:25.548 --> 00:24:28.694
Oh. yeah. Consider the rum
my contribution.

444
00:24:28.718 --> 00:24:33.824
Elle did everything else.
and I mean... everything else.

445
00:24:33.848 --> 00:24:35.492
How's Shannon doing?

446
00:24:35.516 --> 00:24:37.953
It seems like she's really
keeping it together.

447
00:24:37.977 --> 00:24:39.663
Have you still not checked in on her?

448
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:40.980
I've been giving her space.

449
00:24:42.148 --> 00:24:46.128
I don't know if I've been
a good friend to her lately.

450
00:24:46.152 --> 00:24:48.922
Yeah. well. she's putting on a brave face.

451
00:24:48.946 --> 00:24:50.924
Her mom died.

452
00:24:50.948 --> 00:24:52.843
It doesn't matter that she dumped you.

453
00:24:52.867 --> 00:24:54.994
Give her a hug and get over yourself.

454
00:24:57.079 --> 00:24:59.498
I... will do that.

455
00:25:00.917 --> 00:25:03.478
Does that have rum in it?

456
00:25:03.502 --> 00:25:06.982
Um... that depends.

457
00:25:07.006 --> 00:25:11.195
Who's asking? Elle or Sandra Day O'Connor?

458
00:25:11.219 --> 00:25:13.906
That's Justice O'Connor to you.

459
00:25:13.930 --> 00:25:17.743
And please do me a favor
and stop everyone from getting wasted.

460
00:25:17.767 --> 00:25:20.728
I can't stay. and I don't want
Robin's memorial to go off the rails.

461
00:25:21.312 --> 00:25:23.064
I'm all over it. Your Honor.

462
00:25:25.358 --> 00:25:26.400
Thank you.

463
00:25:41.415 --> 00:25:42.392
Are you high?

464
00:25:42.416 --> 00:25:44.853
You know. people are saying
these are baby alligators.

465
00:25:44.877 --> 00:25:47.481
but I'm pretty sure...

466
00:25:47.505 --> 00:25:49.733
that these are baby crocodiles.

467
00:25:49.757 --> 00:25:51.485
Yeah. those are crocodiles.

468
00:25:51.509 --> 00:25:53.219
They look just like a purse I have.

469
00:25:54.929 --> 00:25:56.114
You're Dustin.

470
00:25:56.138 --> 00:25:59.117
-Yeah.
-You're edgy.

471
00:25:59.141 --> 00:26:02.812
You skateboard.
You love causes. et cetera.

472
00:26:04.063 --> 00:26:06.291
I'm Madison.

473
00:26:06.315 --> 00:26:08.126
Hi.

474
00:26:08.150 --> 00:26:09.443
LeDoux.

475
00:26:10.528 --> 00:26:13.423
And I'm Elle's best friend from L.A.

476
00:26:13.447 --> 00:26:18.095
You know. L.A. nine. Seattle 11.

477
00:26:18.119 --> 00:26:21.831
I'm sorry. I really
haven't heard of you before.

478
00:26:26.752 --> 00:26:29.982
So let's just go back to the part
where I'm sexy and edgy?

479
00:26:30.006 --> 00:26:31.608
I didn't say sexy.

480
00:26:31.632 --> 00:26:33.301
Yeah. it was implied.

481
00:26:35.219 --> 00:26:36.220
Huh.

482
00:26:51.986 --> 00:26:53.446
What's up. Lizbian?

483
00:26:54.280 --> 00:26:56.282
Not sure I love that coming from you.

484
00:26:57.867 --> 00:27:00.369
And it's. um. Monica Geller.

485
00:27:01.037 --> 00:27:02.264
Right.

486
00:27:02.288 --> 00:27:04.850
Nice touch. by the way.

487
00:27:04.874 --> 00:27:06.852
It's been. um.
giving everyone an icebreaker

488
00:27:06.876 --> 00:27:08.520
that isn't. like. a total bummer.

489
00:27:08.544 --> 00:27:14.234
It's actually Elle sprinkling
her little fairy dust all over everything.

490
00:27:14.258 --> 00:27:16.945
God. why do I keep giving her
compliments?

491
00:27:16.969 --> 00:27:18.030
Tell no one.

492
00:27:18.054 --> 00:27:20.389
Your secret's safe with me.

493
00:27:27.646 --> 00:27:30.524
Um... I'm sorry about Robin.

494
00:27:31.817 --> 00:27:35.446
I remember how she used to send you those
rad care packages when we were at camp.

495
00:27:36.739 --> 00:27:38.633
How are you holding up?

496
00:27:38.657 --> 00:27:40.910
Um...

497
00:27:43.537 --> 00:27:46.290
Yeah. no one's actually asked me that yet.

498
00:27:52.380 --> 00:27:53.506
I'm terrible.

499
00:27:55.299 --> 00:27:57.802
My mom sucks. and. uh...

500
00:27:58.928 --> 00:28:02.139
I told Robin things
I could never tell my parents.

501
00:28:04.642 --> 00:28:09.313
You know. there are things
that I didn't say that I-I wish I said.

502
00:28:11.023 --> 00:28:14.068
So many things to-to say. you know?

503
00:28:15.069 --> 00:28:18.090
Um. hey. have you had anything to eat?

504
00:28:18.114 --> 00:28:19.424
-Hmm?
-Or drink?

505
00:28:19.448 --> 00:28:21.951
You know. anything age-appropriate?

506
00:28:25.371 --> 00:28:27.099
Oh.

507
00:28:27.123 --> 00:28:30.018
It was so nice to meet you.

508
00:28:30.042 --> 00:28:31.478
Elle.

509
00:28:31.502 --> 00:28:32.979
Excuse me.

510
00:28:33.003 --> 00:28:35.107
I am so sorry for your loss.

511
00:28:35.131 --> 00:28:36.632
Thank you.

512
00:28:39.635 --> 00:28:41.822
-Can we go now?
-Yes.

513
00:28:41.846 --> 00:28:44.783
I just need to make sure there's still ink
in the pen for the condolence journal.

514
00:28:44.807 --> 00:28:47.828
Don't you have a co-planner?
Who cares about ink?

515
00:28:47.852 --> 00:28:50.789
Someone writing a heartfelt message
of sympathy is-is very important.

516
00:28:50.813 --> 00:28:53.250
I mean. I don't care.

517
00:28:53.274 --> 00:28:56.128
Me. Your best friend.

518
00:28:56.152 --> 00:29:00.340
And guest. and person who was excited
about this trip for three months.

519
00:29:00.364 --> 00:29:02.700
I don't care about
the stupid condolence pen.

520
00:29:04.660 --> 00:29:08.080
I've just never known anyone
who's died before.

521
00:29:08.831 --> 00:29:11.959
I guess making sure everything's perfect
is my way of helping.

522
00:29:13.544 --> 00:29:15.147
But you're right. we can go.

523
00:29:15.171 --> 00:29:17.423
Liz and Dustin didn't even know who I was.

524
00:29:19.216 --> 00:29:21.570
I came here on my fall break
to see my best friend

525
00:29:21.594 --> 00:29:25.740
because I really missed you. and...

526
00:29:25.764 --> 00:29:27.433
I feel like I don't even exist.

527
00:29:28.184 --> 00:29:29.327
-Madison.
-Why didn't you tell me

528
00:29:29.351 --> 00:29:31.228
you aren't applying
to the Cosmo internship?

529
00:29:31.812 --> 00:29:34.332
Well. I-I was. I was going
to tell you. but I...

530
00:29:34.356 --> 00:29:36.501
But you didn't. Your dad did.

531
00:29:36.525 --> 00:29:38.587
Did you even remember I was coming?

532
00:29:38.611 --> 00:29:40.046
Of course I remembered you were coming.

533
00:29:40.070 --> 00:29:41.214
-No. you didn't.
-We planned...

534
00:29:41.238 --> 00:29:44.217
I swear. you're the only person that's
ever left L.A. and started lying more.

535
00:29:44.241 --> 00:29:45.969
Okay.

536
00:29:45.993 --> 00:29:47.411
Fine.

537
00:29:48.621 --> 00:29:50.039
I forgot. okay?

538
00:29:51.207 --> 00:29:55.061
And I know I haven't kept you
up to speed as much as you'd like.

539
00:29:55.085 --> 00:29:57.647
but headline. things have been
really. really hard here.

540
00:29:57.671 --> 00:29:59.465
Then why do you want to stay?

541
00:30:01.884 --> 00:30:06.764
Because... somewhere along the way.
I started to like it.

542
00:30:09.517 --> 00:30:11.310
I feel like I don't even know you.

543
00:30:13.521 --> 00:30:15.940
When you're ready to be Elle Woods again.
give me a call.

544
00:30:18.484 --> 00:30:19.503
Madison. hang on.

545
00:30:19.527 --> 00:30:20.587
Check. check.

546
00:30:20.611 --> 00:30:22.464
Oh.

547
00:30:22.488 --> 00:30:27.284
Echo. echo. echo. Echo.

548
00:30:29.036 --> 00:30:31.139
Sorry.

549
00:30:31.163 --> 00:30:37.187
Uh. we have now entered
the urology portion of the evening.

550
00:30:37.211 --> 00:30:39.022
-Urology? Urology?
-Is she wasted?

551
00:30:39.046 --> 00:30:41.316
-Eulogy?
-Ye...

552
00:30:41.340 --> 00:30:43.968
Thank you. Eu-lol...

553
00:30:44.969 --> 00:30:46.696
Whatever. I'm-I'm-a talk for a minute.

554
00:30:46.720 --> 00:30:47.781
Mm. Help her.

555
00:30:47.805 --> 00:30:50.158
Do you remember
the part of Robin's book

556
00:30:50.182 --> 00:30:54.454
where that cactus told her
to be true to herself?

557
00:30:54.478 --> 00:30:59.275
Well. let me cactus a bit
and be honest with myself to all of you...

558
00:31:00.693 --> 00:31:04.172
Hey. hey. are you okay?

559
00:31:04.196 --> 00:31:06.907
I barfed. Did you see?

560
00:31:07.992 --> 00:31:09.368
What? Did you see that?

561
00:31:11.620 --> 00:31:13.723
I don't think anyone noticed.

562
00:31:13.747 --> 00:31:15.958
Why don't we get her some water?

563
00:31:26.427 --> 00:31:30.490
I'm probably not the one
who should be speaking right now.

564
00:31:30.514 --> 00:31:35.102
since Robin wasn't my mom.

565
00:31:37.980 --> 00:31:39.565
Or confidante.

566
00:31:41.400 --> 00:31:43.962
Or colleague.

567
00:31:43.986 --> 00:31:49.175
But... whoever Robin was to you.

568
00:31:49.199 --> 00:31:52.202
thank you for being here today
to pay your respects.

569
00:31:56.915 --> 00:31:58.417
Um...

570
00:31:59.585 --> 00:32:01.021
I just...

571
00:32:01.045 --> 00:32:06.359
recently moved to Seattle. and...

572
00:32:06.383 --> 00:32:09.762
I keep learning new things about it.

573
00:32:10.971 --> 00:32:13.617
Like...

574
00:32:13.641 --> 00:32:18.228
like I just learned that you know
it's a clear day when the mountain's out.

575
00:32:19.980 --> 00:32:21.958
Shannon taught me that.

576
00:32:21.982 --> 00:32:23.877
So...

577
00:32:23.901 --> 00:32:29.007
it's kind of cool to know that
some days are gonna be cloudy

578
00:32:29.031 --> 00:32:32.636
and some days are gonna be beautiful.

579
00:32:32.660 --> 00:32:35.639
but the mountain's always gonna be there.

580
00:32:35.663 --> 00:32:38.415
even if you can't see it.

581
00:32:40.459 --> 00:32:43.087
And that's how I feel about Robin.

582
00:32:44.963 --> 00:32:49.677
Her spirit is always
gonna be there in Shannon.

583
00:32:57.851 --> 00:32:59.436
I'm sorry.

584
00:33:04.650 --> 00:33:07.820
♪ Oh...

585
00:33:10.197 --> 00:33:12.759
They told me the elephants
weren't performing today.

586
00:33:12.783 --> 00:33:15.053
♪ When I dance. they call me Macarena ♪

587
00:33:15.077 --> 00:33:17.764
♪ and the boys. they say que estoy buena ♪

588
00:33:17.788 --> 00:33:20.016
♪ They all want me. they can't have me ♪

589
00:33:20.040 --> 00:33:22.185
♪ so they all come and dance beside me ♪

590
00:33:22.209 --> 00:33:24.396
♪ Move with me. chant with me ♪

591
00:33:24.420 --> 00:33:26.380
♪ And if you're good.
I'll take you home with me ♪

592
00:33:27.089 --> 00:33:29.234
♪ Move with me. chant with me ♪

593
00:33:29.258 --> 00:33:31.260
♪ And if you're good.
I'll take you home with me...

594
00:33:38.475 --> 00:33:39.768
♪ Eh. Macarena...

595
00:33:46.734 --> 00:33:49.421
You know. there's a waterfall
in that bathroom.

596
00:33:49.445 --> 00:33:51.589
Like. the urinal's an actual waterfall.

597
00:33:51.613 --> 00:33:54.134
I may never leave this place.

598
00:33:54.158 --> 00:33:56.302
Gross.

599
00:33:56.326 --> 00:33:57.721
Do you want to make out?

600
00:33:57.745 --> 00:33:59.079
Absolutely.

601
00:34:10.883 --> 00:34:12.092
Wyatt?

602
00:34:14.386 --> 00:34:15.554
Wyatt.

603
00:34:19.099 --> 00:34:21.035
Wyatt!

604
00:34:21.059 --> 00:34:22.537
Whoops. I'm sorry.

605
00:34:22.561 --> 00:34:25.373
I got caught up in my grind riff
to "Light My Fire."

606
00:34:25.397 --> 00:34:26.708
I'm making you a blend.

607
00:34:26.732 --> 00:34:29.753
It's floral meets clove
on a brisk autumn morning.

608
00:34:29.777 --> 00:34:32.172
I have no idea what you're talking about.

609
00:34:32.196 --> 00:34:34.323
Trying to get you to like coffee.

610
00:34:35.824 --> 00:34:38.011
Coffee gives me hives. Wyatt.

611
00:34:38.035 --> 00:34:40.263
Just like hiking makes me sweaty.

612
00:34:40.287 --> 00:34:42.098
and meditating makes me nervous.

613
00:34:42.122 --> 00:34:44.559
and my husband trying
to turn me into a Seattlephile

614
00:34:44.583 --> 00:34:47.353
-is making me want to scream.
-I'm sorry.

615
00:34:47.377 --> 00:34:50.106
I thought that Robin's death
was a wake-up call

616
00:34:50.130 --> 00:34:52.150
to tap into your adventurous side.

617
00:34:52.174 --> 00:34:53.943
That was your interpretation.

618
00:34:53.967 --> 00:34:59.532
Robin's death was my wake-up call
to admit I don't actually feel very alive.

619
00:34:59.556 --> 00:35:00.933
Honey.

620
00:35:02.017 --> 00:35:05.229
I'm having a hard time thinking
of a more vivacious person.

621
00:35:06.396 --> 00:35:08.666
You are the center
of every cocktail party.

622
00:35:08.690 --> 00:35:10.627
You are the queen of the tennis club.

623
00:35:10.651 --> 00:35:14.422
You've never met a task you couldn't fix
with your tenacity and Rolodex.

624
00:35:14.446 --> 00:35:17.050
You just described my life in Bel Air.

625
00:35:17.074 --> 00:35:19.636
Ever since we moved here.

626
00:35:19.660 --> 00:35:21.554
my life's just been on pause.

627
00:35:21.578 --> 00:35:23.097
I haven't felt that way at all.

628
00:35:23.121 --> 00:35:25.666
That's because yours has been on play.

629
00:35:28.377 --> 00:35:29.604
-How was it?
-Fine.

630
00:35:29.628 --> 00:35:31.105
That's bad.

631
00:35:31.129 --> 00:35:33.358
She said it was fine.

632
00:35:33.382 --> 00:35:36.927
Yeah. that's code for "catastrophic."

633
00:35:48.647 --> 00:35:51.042
Do you want to tell me why
Madison's in the basement

634
00:35:51.066 --> 00:35:53.777
watching Sleepless in Seattle by herself?

635
00:35:55.028 --> 00:35:57.173
Because it's more fun
than going to a memorial

636
00:35:57.197 --> 00:35:59.717
of someone that you don't know.

637
00:35:59.741 --> 00:36:03.012
-I ruined her trip.
-Oh...

638
00:36:03.036 --> 00:36:07.308
You still have all weekend together.

639
00:36:07.332 --> 00:36:11.563
Why don't we take
a houseboat cruise tomorrow?

640
00:36:11.587 --> 00:36:16.317
You do know that "houseboat cruise"
isn't a euphemism for yacht. right?

641
00:36:16.341 --> 00:36:18.820
No. I did not.

642
00:36:18.844 --> 00:36:20.220
Huh.

643
00:36:23.056 --> 00:36:24.349
How'd the memorial go?

644
00:36:25.058 --> 00:36:27.537
-Shannon loved it.
-Aw.

645
00:36:27.561 --> 00:36:30.707
The name tag icebreaker worked out great.

646
00:36:30.731 --> 00:36:33.960
And who knew that an animatronic elephant

647
00:36:33.984 --> 00:36:36.236
was the unexpected
joyful moment we all needed?

648
00:36:44.244 --> 00:36:45.996
But you still feel sad.

649
00:36:48.081 --> 00:36:49.082
Mm-hmm.

650
00:36:50.292 --> 00:36:52.753
I just don't know if it was enough.

651
00:36:57.215 --> 00:37:01.511
I wanted to fix things by helping. but...

652
00:37:04.097 --> 00:37:05.783
I know it was just a Band-Aid.

653
00:37:05.807 --> 00:37:08.244
By showing up this way for Shannon.

654
00:37:08.268 --> 00:37:10.538
and for Kimberly. for that matter.

655
00:37:10.562 --> 00:37:13.333
you've helped in ways

656
00:37:13.357 --> 00:37:15.001
I don't think you can understand

657
00:37:15.025 --> 00:37:18.129
until you've gone through
something like this yourself.

658
00:37:18.153 --> 00:37:20.155
-You think so?
-Yeah.

659
00:37:26.119 --> 00:37:28.330
I'm really proud of you.

660
00:37:31.500 --> 00:37:34.711
Hey. uh. you need help
taking this to your car?

661
00:37:35.712 --> 00:37:37.857
That'd be great. Thanks.

662
00:37:37.881 --> 00:37:40.652
Kimberly was supposed
to do cleanup. but...

663
00:37:40.676 --> 00:37:44.054
Yeah. I think. uh.
someone's mom took her home.

664
00:37:45.138 --> 00:37:46.532
Tomorrow's gonna be rough for her.

665
00:37:46.556 --> 00:37:48.409
I'm more worried
about the baby alligators.

666
00:37:48.433 --> 00:37:49.810
I think they're crocodiles.

667
00:37:55.691 --> 00:37:57.567
-I kissed Elle.
-What?

668
00:37:58.652 --> 00:38:01.822
After homecoming. I. uh. I kissed Elle.

669
00:38:03.490 --> 00:38:04.950
Why are you telling me this?

670
00:38:05.534 --> 00:38:07.220
Uh...

671
00:38:07.244 --> 00:38:11.808
Because I-I felt like a...
a dick being here.

672
00:38:11.832 --> 00:38:13.351
keeping a secret from you.

673
00:38:13.375 --> 00:38:15.395
Well. here's an idea.
you wouldn't feel like a dick

674
00:38:15.419 --> 00:38:16.878
if you weren't kissing my friends.

675
00:38:18.922 --> 00:38:21.776
Uh... [scoffs] Okay.

676
00:38:21.800 --> 00:38:25.989
To be fair... you broke up with me.

677
00:38:26.013 --> 00:38:29.683
To be fair.
that was. like. five minutes ago.

678
00:38:32.728 --> 00:38:35.313
So. this is why you've been so weird.

679
00:38:37.190 --> 00:38:39.627
You started liking Elle.

680
00:38:39.651 --> 00:38:43.798
A-And she's just. what.
letting you kiss her?

681
00:38:43.822 --> 00:38:46.676
My so-called friend making out
with my ex behind my back?

682
00:38:46.700 --> 00:38:48.177
-Shannon. it just sort of happened.
-Please.

683
00:38:48.201 --> 00:38:50.722
No. no. she-she wanted to be
the one to tell you first. I j...

684
00:38:50.746 --> 00:38:52.598
-I-I felt like it should come from me.
-Stop.

685
00:38:52.622 --> 00:38:55.768
Stop acting like
this is about doing me some favor.

686
00:38:55.792 --> 00:39:00.672
This is about you two feeling like
shitty friends. mostly because you are.

687
00:39:03.341 --> 00:39:04.468
Shannon.

688
00:39:06.511 --> 00:39:08.489
-Shannon. I'm sorry.
-Get out.

689
00:39:08.513 --> 00:39:11.492
-No. just let me take this to your car...
-Get away from me. Miles!

690
00:39:11.516 --> 00:39:14.603
-We didn't mean to hurt you. Shannon.
-I'm at my mom's memorial.

691
00:39:15.687 --> 00:39:17.397
I am broken.

692
00:39:20.275 --> 00:39:22.444
I am devastated.

693
00:39:23.528 --> 00:39:27.300
And you choose now to tell me this?

694
00:39:27.324 --> 00:39:31.429
It felt like lying to you would be worse.
and... y-you seemed good.

695
00:39:31.453 --> 00:39:34.182
You wanted to believe I was good

696
00:39:34.206 --> 00:39:37.226
so I could cleanse you of your sins
and give you my blessing.

697
00:39:37.250 --> 00:39:39.896
Well. guess what.

698
00:39:39.920 --> 00:39:41.838
I don't want to look at you.

699
00:39:42.464 --> 00:39:45.151
I don't want to be around you.
and you can tell Elle thanks

700
00:39:45.175 --> 00:39:47.945
for her help tonight.
but I am done with her. too.

701
00:39:47.969 --> 00:39:50.722
Shannon. please. Shannon.

702
00:40:04.194 --> 00:40:05.987
-Hi.
-Hi.

703
00:40:06.822 --> 00:40:08.091
Is everything all right?

704
00:40:08.115 --> 00:40:09.741
I. um...

705
00:40:10.867 --> 00:40:12.011
I did something.

706
00:40:12.035 --> 00:40:13.411
Okay.

707
00:40:14.329 --> 00:40:15.389
I told Shannon.

708
00:40:15.413 --> 00:40:17.308
-Please don't tell me you mean...
-No. I told her about us.

709
00:40:17.332 --> 00:40:19.894
Okay.

710
00:40:19.918 --> 00:40:23.022
Um. I-I told you to let me talk to her.

711
00:40:23.046 --> 00:40:25.566
I've known her my whole life.
I-I just wanted it to come from me.

712
00:40:25.590 --> 00:40:27.985
You don't spring this on someone
at their mom's memorial.

713
00:40:28.009 --> 00:40:30.154
I know that...

714
00:40:30.178 --> 00:40:31.239
now.

715
00:40:31.263 --> 00:40:33.449
So now. not only did I break girl code
by kissing her ex.

716
00:40:33.473 --> 00:40:36.476
I broke it again by failing
to tell her I kissed her ex.

717
00:40:37.060 --> 00:40:38.937
I don't want to lose Shannon as a friend.

718
00:40:39.521 --> 00:40:40.564
Me. either.

719
00:40:42.732 --> 00:40:44.085
I don't know what to do.

720
00:40:44.109 --> 00:40:45.402
Nothing. okay?

721
00:40:46.611 --> 00:40:49.132
I will fix this. I will...

722
00:40:49.156 --> 00:40:51.908
talk to her on Monday
and I will smooth this out.

723
00:40:53.785 --> 00:40:57.098
Just do me a favor. and please...

724
00:40:57.122 --> 00:40:59.791
please don't open your mouth
for the next 48 hours.

725
00:41:17.267 --> 00:41:19.120
Boys are so dumb.

726
00:41:19.144 --> 00:41:20.812
So dumb.

727
00:41:21.563 --> 00:41:22.564
Come here.

728
00:41:28.612 --> 00:41:29.672
I love you.

729
00:41:29.696 --> 00:41:31.323
I love you. too.

730
00:41:44.169 --> 00:41:46.856
Where's Shannon? Why are you
rummaging through her locker?

731
00:41:46.880 --> 00:41:48.274
I'm not rummaging. I'm cleaning.

732
00:41:48.298 --> 00:41:50.342
And before you ask.
no. I do not need your help.

733
00:41:50.967 --> 00:41:52.278
Why would you need my help?

734
00:41:52.302 --> 00:41:55.031
Sorry. I-I-I don't mean to be. like.

735
00:41:55.055 --> 00:41:58.367
you know. um...
It's just that I'm. like. freaking out.

736
00:41:58.391 --> 00:42:01.329
Um. I guess
you're friends with her.

737
00:42:01.353 --> 00:42:03.623
but I've known her since kindergarten.

738
00:42:03.647 --> 00:42:04.999
I-I didn't just expect her to...

739
00:42:05.023 --> 00:42:06.417
Well. I don't know
what you're talking about.

740
00:42:06.441 --> 00:42:08.002
I'm talking about my best friend
skipping town.

741
00:42:08.026 --> 00:42:09.337
Wait. what?

742
00:42:09.361 --> 00:42:11.464
Shannon went to her dad's in Denver.

743
00:42:11.488 --> 00:42:14.175
That can't be...
I really need to talk to her.

744
00:42:14.199 --> 00:42:16.886
-Join the club.
-No. like. I really need to talk to her.

745
00:42:16.910 --> 00:42:18.846
-When is she coming back?
-You don't understand.

746
00:42:18.870 --> 00:42:21.057
Shannon went to her dad's
in Denver to live.

747
00:42:21.081 --> 00:42:24.334
She moved. Shannon's not coming back.

748
00:42:37.889 --> 00:42:39.116
Hi. Good morning.

749
00:42:39.140 --> 00:42:40.475
Morning.

750
00:42:45.772 --> 00:42:47.649
I'm doing this for you. Elle.

751
00:42:48.358 --> 00:42:49.919
Hey.

752
00:42:49.943 --> 00:42:52.630
I'm doing this for you. too.

753
00:42:52.654 --> 00:42:54.698
We belong in L.A.

754
00:42:56.700 --> 00:42:59.470
♪ I dreamt ♪

755
00:42:59.494 --> 00:43:04.475
♪ you chased down the car ♪

756
00:43:04.499 --> 00:43:11.232
♪ waving a sign that made no sense ♪

757
00:43:11.256 --> 00:43:17.196
